{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01GyFCcB2wPWMh58P6QwhGSP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ **PASS** — all 15 obligations proved, no cheating detected.\n\nThe proof is the classic Cantor diagonalization argument. The key insight is choosing the witness set\n$$A = \\{x \\in S : x \\notin f[x]\\}$$\n— the elements that are *not* members of their own image under $f$.\n\nThe proof structure:\n- `<1>1` — $A$ is a subset of $S$ (trivially, by its set-builder form), so it's a valid existential witness.\n- `<1>2` — for any $x \\in S$, $f[x] \\neq A$, proven by contradiction: assume $f[x] = A$, then membership $x \\in A \\iff x \\notin f[x]$ (by definition of $A$) collides with $x \\in A \\iff x \\in f[x]$ (from $f[x]=A$), giving the paradox.\n- The final `QED` lets TLAPS discharge the bounded existential `\\E A \\in SUBSET S : ...` using $A$ as the witness.\n\nOnly the placeholder `PROOF OBVIOUS` was replaced — the module header, theorem statement, and declarations are untouched, and no `OMITTED` was used."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":131,"cache_creation_input_tokens":777,"cache_read_input_tokens":21973,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":777},"output_tokens":46,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5781181f-e4bb-4d73-bb0d-98ec01d2874d","uuid":"5ccd640e-5203-4771-a339-5f6d303ff6b1","request_id":"req_011CbTyJjEq1vnQW8qYe3CdH"}
